\ demo-conway.6th — Conway's Game of Life: blinker oscillation on substrate grid.
\
\ Claim demonstrated:
\   Conway's Game of Life — Turing-complete 2D CA — is expressible
\   directly on the substrate using a 5×5 grid with Moore (8-neighbour)
\   connectivity.  Same STEP-CA primitive that drove Rule 90 and
\   Rule 110 drives Conway with no modification.
\
\   Conway rule:
\     live cell stays alive iff neighbours ∈ {2, 3}
\     dead cell becomes alive iff neighbours = 3
\
\   Verified pattern: BLINKER — three live cells in a vertical column
\   oscillate to horizontal then back, period 2.
\
\   Substrate primitives used:  NSUM (count live neighbours via OUT-edges).

: 2dup over over ;
: nip swap drop ;
: not 0 = ;
: 1+ 1 + ;

: bi-edge 2dup EDGE+ swap EDGE+ ;

\ Conway rule via STEP-CA
\ next = (NSUM == 3) ? 1 : ((NSUM == 2 AND state == 1) ? 1 : 0)
: conway
  dup NSUM "_sum" store
  NGET "_st" store
  "_sum" load 3 = if 1 else
    "_sum" load 2 = "_st" load 1 = * if 1 else 0 then
  then ;

\ ─── build 5×5 grid (25 nodes, ids 1..25 in row-major order) ───
\ Cells: (i,j) → node id (i-1)*5 + j
\ Layout: row 1 = ids 1..5, row 2 = 6..10, ..., row 5 = 21..25
MARK MARK MARK MARK MARK
MARK MARK MARK MARK MARK
MARK MARK MARK MARK MARK
MARK MARK MARK MARK MARK
MARK MARK MARK MARK MARK
drop drop drop drop drop drop drop drop drop drop
drop drop drop drop drop drop drop drop drop drop
drop drop drop drop drop

NODES 25 = ASSERT

\ Horizontal edges within each row
1 2 bi-edge   2 3 bi-edge   3 4 bi-edge   4 5 bi-edge
6 7 bi-edge   7 8 bi-edge   8 9 bi-edge   9 10 bi-edge
11 12 bi-edge   12 13 bi-edge   13 14 bi-edge   14 15 bi-edge
16 17 bi-edge   17 18 bi-edge   18 19 bi-edge   19 20 bi-edge
21 22 bi-edge   22 23 bi-edge   23 24 bi-edge   24 25 bi-edge

\ Vertical edges within each column
1 6 bi-edge   6 11 bi-edge   11 16 bi-edge   16 21 bi-edge
2 7 bi-edge   7 12 bi-edge   12 17 bi-edge   17 22 bi-edge
3 8 bi-edge   8 13 bi-edge   13 18 bi-edge   18 23 bi-edge
4 9 bi-edge   9 14 bi-edge   14 19 bi-edge   19 24 bi-edge
5 10 bi-edge   10 15 bi-edge   15 20 bi-edge   20 25 bi-edge

\ Diagonal NW-SE
1 7 bi-edge   2 8 bi-edge   3 9 bi-edge   4 10 bi-edge
6 12 bi-edge   7 13 bi-edge   8 14 bi-edge   9 15 bi-edge
11 17 bi-edge   12 18 bi-edge   13 19 bi-edge   14 20 bi-edge
16 22 bi-edge   17 23 bi-edge   18 24 bi-edge   19 25 bi-edge

\ Diagonal NE-SW
2 6 bi-edge   3 7 bi-edge   4 8 bi-edge   5 9 bi-edge
7 11 bi-edge   8 12 bi-edge   9 13 bi-edge   10 14 bi-edge
